JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng province has opened more public vaccination sites this weekend. The number of sites has now increase from 16 to 26; these are sites that are open on the weekend for the first time. Gauteng public vaccination sites are now able to accept walk-ins whether people are registered or not. Health MEC Nomathemba Mokgethi is conducting oversight visits at West Rand vaccination on Saturday. Her spokesperson Motaletale Modiba said: “Gauteng’s vaccination rollout programme is indeed gaining momentum, and this is reflected by the one million record jabs administered during the month of July. With the total number of vaccinations now standing at over two million.” MEC for Health Dr Nomathemba Mokgethi is visiting West Rand  Vaccination sites as they start operating for first time during weekends. Make your way to the nearest vaccination site as per the attached list.#vaccinesaveslives #VaccineRolloutSA #IChooseVaccination pic.twitter.com/E3hPewriYc  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.